File:Â The COVID-19 outbreak originated in the Chinese city of Wuhan in November before spreading globally. JOHANNESBURG - The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has increased to 43,434. The Health Department has reported 60 more COVID-19 related deaths. Seven of the deaths are from Gauteng and 53 from the Western Cape, bringing the total death toll to 908. Over 850,000 tests have been conducted across the country. Health Media Release 5 June 2020 2020 by Travis Richards on Scribd 